‘We’re not hurting anybody,’ says wife of immigrant taken from Georgia church

He was one of at least 20 apprehensions by U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement in Atlanta on Sunday, according to one estimate
Kenia Velásquez speaks with her husband, Wilson Velásquez, who is in ICE custody in Atlanta on Monday, January 27, 2025. Following their call, Kenia learned that her husband has no right to a hearing before a judge and will be transferred to Stewart Detention Center for deportation. (Miguel Martinez/ AJC)
By Lautaro Grinspan and Alia Pharr
Jan 27, 2025

Nearly every week since they settled in metro Atlanta about two years ago, Kenia and Wilson Velásquez attended church service together on Sundays alongside their three children, ages 7, 9, and 13.

This past Sunday, the first since Donald Trump returned to the White House, only part of the family returned home from church. Wilson Velásquez, 36, was arrested by immigration authorities around midday, just as the sermon inside Iglesia Fuente de Vida in Tucker was nearing its end.
